BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 122.97 of the Revised Code be 3
enacted to read as follows: 4
Sec. 122.97. (A) The Ohio international trade commission 5
is created. The commission shall, as between Ohio and Japan, 6
Ireland, Israel, and two other nations designated by the 7
director of development, advance all of the following: 8
(1) Multilateral trade and investment; 9
(2) Joint research agreements on issues of mutual 10
interest, particularly with Israel regarding electronic and 11
cyber warfare capabilities; 12
(3) Business and academic exchanges; 13
(4) Creation of technology centers to promote 14
collaboration between academic and business interests; 15
(5) Mutual economic support; 16
(6) Mutual investment in infrastructure; 17

